    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "OH that's where the tweet came from :P \n\nFrom what I understand of the context, I would say that it's a combination of using string template with the fact we're not updating the key. From what I understand, what's inside the dangerouslySetInnerHTML is considered a blob thus not interpreted, so it won't count in the diff algo against the generated vdom.\n\nWhen we change the key, we are changing what properties are hold in the vdom. So it is considered  different and so the rendering is updated.\n",
